                        "content": "The nurse is assessing a client diagnosed with polycystic kidney disease. The client is discussing disease management strategies used at home. Which client statement would indicate to the nurse there is a need for further teaching?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nPolycystic kidney disease is a hereditary disorder in which cysts repeatedly grow in the nephrons. Clinical manifestations include hypertension, abdominal distention, flank pain, and hematuria, which could be related to cyst rupture. Complications include infection and progression to chronic kidney disease or kidney failure with anuria. Self-management of polycystic kidney disease includes regular blood pressure monitoring, checking daily weights, and notifying the primary health care provider for sudden weight gain. Dietary sodium intake needs to be limited. Pain management is an important component of treating polycystic kidney disease and may include opioid analgesics or acetaminophen. Nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) need to be avoided in this condition, as NSAIDs reduce renal blood flow. Option 1 is appropriate as a measure to limit dietary sodium. Options 2 and 4 are both important parameters to monitor. Therefore, option 3 is the client statement that would require a need for further teaching.",
                        "id": "20684970ddd0416a818acd779d29af96",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "469092bb55154ed3be8e597fdbdb6e7e",
                                "content": "Headache"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
