                        "content": "The nurse is providing dietary education to a client in the early stages of polycystic kidney disease with preserved renal function. Which of the following is the appropriate recommended daily fluid intake for this client?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nPolycystic kidney disease is a hereditary disorder in which cysts repeatedly grow in the nephrons. Early in the disease, clients experience hyperfiltration with decreased urine concentration, nocturia, and low urine specific gravity. Maintaining adequate fluid volume is imperative to reduce vasopressin release, which reduces renal blood flow. Clients with preserved renal function should consume 3 liters of fluids daily to prevent dehydration associated with voiding large amounts of dilute urine early in the disease. Fluid restriction may become necessary if the client progresses to chronic kidney disease. Therefore, option 3 is correct.",
                        "id": "61b12ffc70084e29a2495da4d4d5dd7b",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
